  "steps": [
    "Heat a pressure cooker, add chickpeas, salt, ½ teaspoon red chilli powder, black cardamom, green cardamoms, cloves, cinnamon, bay leaf, 1 tablespoon chole masala and 3 cups water and mix well.",
    "Cover with the lid and cook under pressure, on medium heat, till the pressure is released 5-6 times.",
    "Open the lid once the pressure settles completely. Strain the chickpeas, discard the whole spices and reserve the stock.",
    "Heat ghee in a non-stick kadai, add cumin seeds and once they start to change colour, add onions and mix well. Add salt, mix and sauté till onions turn a golden brown.",
    "Add ginger-garlic paste and green chillies, mix and sauté for 2-3 minutes.",
    "Add tomato puree and mix well. Add ½ teaspoon red chilli powder, turmeric powder, cumin powder, coriander powder, dried mango powder and ½ teaspoon chole masala, mix well, cover and cook till oil separates.",
    "Add boiled chickpeas and mix well. Add 1½ cups chickpea stock, mix well and cook for 2-3 minutes.",
    "Add coriander leaves and mix well. Transfer into a serving bowl, garnish with ginger strips and green chillies and serve hot with paranthe."
  ],
